>
	<p>
		I'm Asif. I build software with AI at a venture firm. Internal tools, AI
		agents, and the plumbing that lets a small team punch above its weight.
	</p>

	<p>
		Most of my work runs through AI coding tools now. I care about the
		unglamorous part: what actually holds up once you ship it, not what demos
		well.
	</p>

	<p>
		This is where I write that down. Building in public, notes on where the AI
		tooling is headed, and every so often something about what all of this does
		to how we think.
	</p>

	<p>Off the clock, I'm a dad of three.</p>
